<br>
Group Call of the Hero has been brought up before.<br>
<br>
Being able to pull all group members to you, regardless of zone, would be great.  I assume it would use a prompt, much like Translocate does, so it can't be used on someone against their will.<br>
<br>
However, there are two major issues with this idea.<br>
1.  Ability to bypass content.  I shouldn't need to go into detail here, it's obvious.<br>
2.  Gate, cast this.  You now have &quot;Translocate: MY bindpoint.&quot;  Verant already told Wizards that they wouldn't like this because of it's ability to bypass content.<br>
3.  You're providing a Magician with the level 14 (used to be 29) Cleric rez, with the added benifit of being able to obtain an XP rez later.  With the &quot;IN TESTING&quot; druid and shaman Complete Heals on Test, this would give the group yet another reason to chose a druid over a Cleric.  &quot;Hey, we're all 60, we'll make back the XP loss, our Mage can Rez.&quot;<br>
<br>
Make the recast long enough, and it's more of a convenience, rather than an instant temp rez every 14 mins.<br>
<br>
If it was limited to within the same zone like CotH is however, I see no problems with it.  Make it activated, and the next CotH you cast on any group member will bring ALL group members to you from within the zone, for double mana cost.  They just need to modify the MGB code slightly. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
